Founded by Greyson — 2026

DinoStudios exists to preserve, document, and celebrate forgotten dinosaur‑themed media, especially the small, quiet, and overlooked creations that shaped childhood imagination.

Our mission is to:

recover lost or obscure dinosaur content

reconstruct worlds that were never archived

identify and document the tools, mods, and assets behind them

protect childhood memories from disappearing

share clear instructions so others can find what was once lost

honor the emotional impact these creations had on the kids who watched them

DinoStudios believes that even the smallest shows — even the ones nobody talked about — deserve to be remembered.
They deserve to be found.
They deserve to be understood.
They deserve to be preserved.

The recovery of Tankee’s Dinos Reborn is the first completed case, proving that one person with determination, curiosity, and heart can bring an entire forgotten world back into the light.

DinoStudios will continue to search, archive, and protect dinosaur media so that no memory, no show, and no world is ever lost again.

This is our mission.
This is our purpose.
This is DinoStudios.
